{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":833,"text":"I'm a neuroscientist, and I study decision-making."},{"time":4710,"text":"I do experiments to test how different chemicals"},{"time":7017,"text":"in the brain influence the choices we make."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10617,"text":"I'm here to tell you the secret to successful decision-making:"},{"time":17365,"text":"a cheese sandwich."},{"time":19603,"text":"That's right. According to scientists, a cheese sandwich"},{"time":23263,"text":"is the solution to all your tough decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26885,"text":"How do I know? I'm the scientist who did the study."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31942,"text":"A few years ago, my colleagues and I were interested"},{"time":34242,"text":"in how a brain chemical called serotonin"},{"time":36535,"text":"would influence people's decisions in social situations."},{"time":39805,"text":"Specifically, we wanted to know how serotonin would affect"},{"time":42900,"text":"the way people react when they're treated unfairly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46715,"text":"So we did an experiment."},{"time":48253,"text":"We manipulated people's serotonin levels by giving them"},{"time":51399,"text":"this really disgusting-tasting artificial lemon-flavored drink"},{"time":56022,"text":"that works by taking away the raw ingredient for serotonin"},{"time":59654,"text":"in the brain."},{"time":60832,"text":"This is the amino acid tryptophan."},{"time":63809,"text":"So what we found was, when tryptophan was low,"},{"time":66170,"text":"people were more likely to take revenge"},{"time":68622,"text":"when they're treated unfairly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72170,"text":"That's the study we did, and here are some of the headlines"},{"time":75993,"text":"that came out afterwards."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78722,"text":"(\"A cheese sandwich is all you need for strong decision-making\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":81217,"text":"(\"What a friend we have in cheeses\")"}]},{"cues":[{"time":83312,"text":"(\"Eating Cheese and Meat May Boost Self-Control\") At this point, you might be wondering, did I miss something?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86512,"text":"(\"Official! Chocolate stops you being grumpy\") Cheese? Chocolate? Where did that come from?"},{"time":91907,"text":"And I thought the same thing myself when these came out,"},{"time":94040,"text":"because our study had nothing to do with cheese or chocolate."},{"time":98285,"text":"We gave people this horrible-tasting drink"},{"time":100614,"text":"that affected their tryptophan levels."},{"time":103816,"text":"But it turns out that tryptophan also happens to be found"},{"time":107497,"text":"in cheese and chocolate."},{"time":110298,"text":"And of course when science says cheese and chocolate"},{"time":112608,"text":"help you make better decisions, well, that's sure to grab people's attention."},{"time":116689,"text":"So there you have it:"},{"time":118656,"text":"the evolution of a headline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122163,"text":"When this happened, a part of me thought, well,"},{"time":124505,"text":"what's the big deal?"},{"time":126509,"text":"So the media oversimplified a few things, but in the end,"},{"time":130388,"text":"it's just a news story."},{"time":132464,"text":"And I think a lot of scientists have this attitude."},{"time":135817,"text":"But the problem is that this kind of thing happens all the time,"},{"time":139714,"text":"and it affects not just the stories you read in the news"},{"time":142841,"text":"but also the products you see on the shelves."},{"time":145620,"text":"When the headlines rolled, what happened was,"},{"time":148287,"text":"the marketers came calling."},{"time":151113,"text":"Would I be willing to provide a scientific endorsement"},{"time":154332,"text":"of a mood-boosting bottled water?"},{"time":157593,"text":"Or would I go on television to demonstrate,"},{"time":159737,"text":"in front of a live audience,"},{"time":160762,"text":"that comfort foods really do make you feel better?"},{"time":164361,"text":"I think these folks meant well, but had I taken them up on their offers,"},{"time":168322,"text":"I would have been going beyond the science,"},{"time":170696,"text":"and good scientists are careful not to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173953,"text":"But nevertheless, neuroscience is turning up more and more in marketing."},{"time":178321,"text":"Here's one example: Neuro drinks,"},{"time":180881,"text":"a line of products, including Nuero Bliss here,"},{"time":184122,"text":"which according to its label helps reduce stress,"},{"time":187023,"text":"enhances mood, provides focused concentration,"},{"time":190449,"text":"and promotes a positive outlook."},{"time":193137,"text":"I have to say, this sounds awesome. (Laughter)"},{"time":197762,"text":"I could totally have used this 10 minutes ago."},{"time":201638,"text":"So when this came up in my local shop, naturally I was"},{"time":205068,"text":"curious about some of the research backing these claims."},{"time":208617,"text":"So I went to the company's website looking to find"},{"time":211543,"text":"some controlled trials of their products."},{"time":214969,"text":"But I didn't find any."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216646,"text":"Trial or no trial, these claims are front and center"},{"time":220384,"text":"on their label right next to a picture of a brain."},{"time":224346,"text":"And it turns out that pictures of brains have special properties."},{"time":230049,"text":"A couple of researchers asked a few hundred people"},{"time":232511,"text":"to read a scientific article."},{"time":235202,"text":"For half the people, the article included a brain image,"},{"time":238529,"text":"and for the other half, it was the same article"},{"time":240392,"text":"but it didn't have a brain image."},{"time":243096,"text":"At the end — you see where this is going —"},{"time":244728,"text":"people were asked whether they agreed"},{"time":246838,"text":"with the conclusions of the article."},{"time":250160,"text":"So this is how much people agree with the conclusions"},{"time":252433,"text":"with no image."},{"time":254346,"text":"And this is how much they agree with the same article"},{"time":257993,"text":"that did include a brain image."},{"time":260760,"text":"So the take-home message here is,"},{"time":262709,"text":"do you want to sell it? Put a brain on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267616,"text":"Now let me pause here and take a moment to say that"},{"time":269729,"text":"neuroscience has advanced a lot in the last few decades,"},{"time":273427,"text":"and we're constantly discovering amazing things"},{"time":275880,"text":"about the brain."},{"time":277153,"text":"Like, just a couple of weeks ago, neuroscientists at MIT"},{"time":280297,"text":"figured out how to break habits in rats"},{"time":283097,"text":"just by controlling neural activity in a specific part of their brain."},{"time":287090,"text":"Really cool stuff."},{"time":288680,"text":"But the promise of neuroscience has led to some really"},{"time":291973,"text":"high expectations and some overblown, unproven claims."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297209,"text":"So what I'm going to do is show you how to spot"},{"time":300248,"text":"a couple of classic moves, dead giveaways, really,"},{"time":303794,"text":"for what's variously been called neuro-bunk,"},{"time":306590,"text":"neuro-bollocks, or, my personal favorite, neuro-flapdoodle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312282,"text":"So the first unproven claim is that you can use brain scans"},{"time":316620,"text":"to read people's thoughts and emotions."},{"time":320532,"text":"Here's a study published by a team of researchers"},{"time":323579,"text":"as an op-ed in The New York Times."},{"time":326412,"text":"The headline? \"You Love Your iPhone. Literally.\""},{"time":330657,"text":"It quickly became the most emailed article on the site."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335107,"text":"So how'd they figure this out?"},{"time":337276,"text":"They put 16 people inside a brain scanner"},{"time":340304,"text":"and showed them videos of ringing iPhones."},{"time":343586,"text":"The brain scans showed activation in a part of the brain"},{"time":347048,"text":"called the insula, a region they say"},{"time":349700,"text":"is linked to feelings of love and compassion."},{"time":353484,"text":"So they concluded that because they saw activation in the insula,"},{"time":357144,"text":"this meant the subjects loved their iPhones."},{"time":361431,"text":"Now there's just one problem with this line of reasoning,"},{"time":363575,"text":"and that's that the insula does a lot."},{"time":367091,"text":"Sure, it is involved in positive emotions"},{"time":369396,"text":"like love and compassion,"},{"time":371738,"text":"but it's also involved in tons of other processes,"},{"time":374411,"text":"like memory, language, attention,"},{"time":377484,"text":"even anger, disgust and pain."},{"time":381520,"text":"So based on the same logic, I could equally conclude"},{"time":385983,"text":"you hate your iPhone."},{"time":388436,"text":"The point here is, when you see activation in the insula,"},{"time":391280,"text":"you can't just pick and choose your favorite explanation"},{"time":394306,"text":"from off this list, and it's a really long list."},{"time":398972,"text":"My colleagues Tal Yarkoni and Russ Poldrack"},{"time":401306,"text":"have shown that the insula pops up in almost a third"},{"time":404428,"text":"of all brain imaging studies that have ever been published."},{"time":409164,"text":"So chances are really, really good"},{"time":410678,"text":"that your insula is going off right now,"},{"time":413804,"text":"but I won't kid myself"},{"time":415426,"text":"to think this means you love me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419103,"text":"So speaking of love and the brain,"},{"time":422010,"text":"there's a researcher, known to some as Dr. Love,"},{"time":425875,"text":"who claims that scientists have found the glue"},{"time":429360,"text":"that holds society together,"},{"time":432007,"text":"the source of love and prosperity."},{"time":435783,"text":"This time it's not a cheese sandwich."},{"time":437972,"text":"No, it's a hormone called oxytocin."},{"time":441829,"text":"You've probably heard of it."},{"time":443696,"text":"So, Dr. Love bases his argument on studies showing"},{"time":446588,"text":"that when you boost people's oxytocin,"},{"time":449533,"text":"this increases their trust, empathy and cooperation."},{"time":453706,"text":"So he's calling oxytocin \"the moral molecule.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":457786,"text":"Now these studies are scientifically valid,"},{"time":460628,"text":"and they've been replicated, but they're not the whole story."},{"time":464764,"text":"Other studies have shown that boosting oxytocin"},{"time":467477,"text":"increases envy. It increases gloating."},{"time":472220,"text":"Oxytocin can bias people to favor their own group"},{"time":475536,"text":"at the expense of other groups."},{"time":478628,"text":"And in some cases, oxytocin can even decrease cooperation."},{"time":482880,"text":"So based on these studies, I could say oxytocin"},{"time":486700,"text":"is an immoral molecule, and call myself Dr. Strangelove."},{"time":491451,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494811,"text":"So we've seen neuro-flapdoodle all over the headlines."},{"time":498921,"text":"We see it in supermarkets, on book covers."},{"time":501699,"text":"What about the clinic?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504370,"text":"SPECT imaging is a brain-scanning technology"},{"time":507785,"text":"that uses a radioactive tracer"},{"time":509854,"text":"to track blood flow in the brain."},{"time":512894,"text":"For the bargain price of a few thousand dollars,"},{"time":515978,"text":"there are clinics in the U.S. that will give you"},{"time":520096,"text":"one of these SPECT scans and use the image"},{"time":523549,"text":"to help diagnose your problems."},{"time":526186,"text":"These scans, the clinics say, can help"},{"time":528715,"text":"prevent Alzheimer's disease,"},{"time":531617,"text":"solve weight and addiction issues,"},{"time":534081,"text":"overcome marital conflicts,"},{"time":536753,"text":"and treat, of course, a variety of mental illnesses"},{"time":539903,"text":"ranging from depression to anxiety to ADHD."},{"time":543482,"text":"This sounds great. A lot of people agree."},{"time":546052,"text":"Some of these clinics are pulling in tens of millions"},{"time":548218,"text":"of dollars a year in business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551522,"text":"There's just one problem."},{"time":553606,"text":"The broad consensus in neuroscience"},{"time":556283,"text":"is that we can't yet diagnose mental illness"},{"time":559468,"text":"from a single brain scan."},{"time":562251,"text":"But these clinics have treated"},{"time":564482,"text":"tens of thousands of patients to date,"},{"time":566922,"text":"many of them children,"},{"time":568684,"text":"and SPECT imaging involves a radioactive injection,"},{"time":572162,"text":"so exposing people to radiation, potentially harmful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578159,"text":"I am more excited than most people, as a neuroscientist,"},{"time":581273,"text":"about the potential for neuroscience to treat mental illness"},{"time":585554,"text":"and even maybe to make us better and smarter."},{"time":590278,"text":"And if one day we can say that cheese and chocolate"},{"time":592978,"text":"help us make better decisions, count me in."},{"time":597282,"text":"But we're not there yet."},{"time":599858,"text":"We haven't found a \"buy\" button inside the brain,"},{"time":603593,"text":"we can't tell whether someone is lying or in love"},{"time":607291,"text":"just by looking at their brain scans,"},{"time":610674,"text":"and we can't turn sinners into saints with hormones."},{"time":614938,"text":"Maybe someday we will, but until then,"},{"time":617142,"text":"we have to be careful that we don't let overblown claims"},{"time":619985,"text":"detract resources and attention away from the real science"},{"time":623371,"text":"that's playing a much longer game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627130,"text":"So here's where you come in."},{"time":629568,"text":"If someone tries to sell you something with a brain on it,"},{"time":632739,"text":"don't just take them at their word."},{"time":635618,"text":"Ask the tough questions. Ask to see the evidence."},{"time":638864,"text":"Ask for the part of the story that's not being told."},{"time":642762,"text":"The answers shouldn't be simple, because the brain isn't simple."},{"time":647850,"text":"But that's not stopping us from trying to figure it out anyway."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652345,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}